'","derivation":"a primitive root;","strongs_def":"to expand","kjv_def":"all abroad, enlarge, spread, stretch out.","pos":"verb","usage":"spread(3x), enlarge(1x)"},"H7850":{"id":"H7850","lemma":"שֹׁטֵט","translit":"shôṭêṭ","pron":"sho-tate'","derivation":"active participle of an otherwise unused root meaning (properly, to pierce; but only as a denominative from H7752 (שׁוֹט))","strongs_def":"to flog; a goad","kjv_def":"scourge.","pos":"masculine noun","usage":"scourge(1x)"},"H7851":{"id":"H7851","lemma":"שִׁטִּים","translit":"Shiṭṭîym","pron":"shit-teem'","derivation":"the same as the plural of H7848 (שִׁטָּה); acacia trees;","strongs_def":"Shittim, a place East of the Jordan","kjv_def":"Shittim.","pos":"proper locative noun","usage":"Shittim(5x)"},"H7852":{"id":"H7852","lemma":"שָׂטַם","translit":"sâṭam","pron":"saw-tam'","derivation":"a primitive root;","strongs_def":"properly, to lurk for, i.e. persecute","kjv_def":"hate, oppose self against.","pos":"verb","usage":"hate(5x), oppose(1x)"},"H7853":{"id":"H7853","lemma":"שָׂטַן","translit":"sâṭan","pron":"saw-tan'","derivation":"a primitive root;","strongs_def":"to attack, (figuratively) accuse","kjv_def":"(be an) adversary, resist.","pos":"verb","usage":"adversary(5x), resist(1x)"},"H7854":{"id":"H7854","lemma":"שָׂטָן","translit":"sâṭân","pron":"saw-tawn'","derivation":"from H7853 (שָׂטַן);","strongs_def":"an opponent; especially (with the article prefixed) Satan, the arch-enemy of good","kjv_def":"adversary, Satan, withstand.","pos":"masculine noun","usage":"Satan(19x), adversary(7x), withstand(1x)"},"H7855":{"id":"H7855","lemma":"שִׂטְנָה","translit":"siṭnâh","pron":"sit-naw'","derivation":"from H7853 (שָׂטַן);","strongs_def":"opposition (by letter)","kjv_def":"accusation.","pos":"feminine noun","usage":"accusation(1x)"},"H7856":{"id":"H7856","lemma":"שִׂטְנָה","translit":"Siṭnâh","pron":"sit-naw'","derivation":"the same as H7855 (שִׂטְנָה);","strongs_def":"Sitnah, the name of a well in Pal","kjv_def":"Sitnah."}